## Core Interview Flow

```
AI plays question audio (TTS via OpenAI)
    ↓
Audio queue ends → auto-listen starts (Silero VAD on recording stream)
    ↓
12s dead-silence detector (Silero — not FFT energy)
    │
    ├─ User speaks within 12s
    │       ↓  speech detected
    │   Recording in progress (waveform bars animate)
    │       ↓  5s of silence after speech ends
    │   Auto-submit — no button press needed
    │       ↓
    │   POST /api/interview/submit-answer-realtime
    │       ↓
    │   Orchestrator → Decision Engine → TTS → buildAudioQueue(isFollowUp)
    │       ↓
    │   GlowingOrb pulses → audio ends → auto-listen restarts
    │
    └─ No speech for 12s
            ↓
        LLM rephrase (text on screen + TTS) → fresh 12s listen window
            ↓  still silent
        Motivation TTS only (no banner text) → skip submit → next question
            ↓  3 consecutive silent skips
        Wrap-up TTS → Feedback

Parallel: Video presence monitor (from Start Interview → end)
    3s out of frame → warning TTS + banner, clock resets
    10s still out → countdown → wrap-up → Feedback
    Return to frame → resume listening (see presenceMonitor.js)
```

> **Audio bus:** Only one interviewer clip at a time. `stopAllAIAudio()` + `interviewActiveRef`. Presence warnings defer if question/motivation is playing. Never set `interviewActiveRef = false` in `releaseAllMedia()` — only on explicit end.

